Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_3931
Response Text: Well-established arts and cultural organizations must be supported financially in order for it to be financially viable to produce professional work,  hire more creatives, and attract more visitors, all of which contributs to the local economy.  Austin lacks diverse funding for non-profit cultural organizations, relative to the size of the city.  ACME can help by diversifying its own financial support of arts organizations.  The arts ecosystem should be supported financially (grants/contracts) and infrastructure assistance (facilitating collaborations for things like rent, in-kind services, etc.) extremely broadly.  Diverse organizations of all budget sizes, organizational age (cultural institutions, established, emerging), and creative discipline must be supported for a healthy creative industry.  Additionally, ACME can help raise the profile of the arts and culture industry that collectively creates an identity that attracts business and visitors, as well as serves as a true economic driver for the region.  I would also suggest that leaders of ACME meet with the arts organizational leaders to get their direct input.

